9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 915, L.D. 1393, “An Act to Require
10 Continuing Education for Licensed Architects”
11 Amend the bill in section 1 in §224-B in subsection 1 in the first line (page 1, line 4 in
12 L.D.) by striking out the following: "As" and inserting the following: 'Beginning July 1,
13 2026, as'
14 Amend the bill in section 1 in §224-B by striking out all of subsection 2 (page 1, lines
15 14 to 21 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
16 '2. Exemption. An architect who receives an initial license to practice architecture
17 from any jurisdiction, including a foreign jurisdiction, is exempt from the requirements of
18 subsection 1 for 2 years from the date of issuance of that initial license, as long as the
19 architect has not been previously licensed by any jurisdiction, including a foreign
20 jurisdiction, for a period of 2 or more years.'
21 Amend the bill by inserting after section 1 the following:
22 'Sec. 2. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
23 allocations are made.
